<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1529">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/45a.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-26">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Telegraph all available information regarding Brothers of the
                                Christian Schools. Reported nineteen teachers of this school, all
                                foreigners, were imprisoned by Constitutionalists because demand for
                                $500,000 not complied with, but later released and forced to leave
                                the country. Teachers now in Havana desire return. Will authorities
                                permit and give protection? What has become of school property?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>